Notes: There is no landing or lading of merchandise, except in time of war when wheat is brought to the mill from Portsmouth to be ground to the Queen's provision.

Two of the 11 unoccupied houses are the best houses in the town. The two ships are both now idle: Lyon used to trade with Scotland for fish; Lyon and Mary traded sometimes to France. All of the boats are occupied in carriage of wood and other necessary provisions for the town; the smaller boats are also sometimes occupied in dragging of oysters.
